						<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Scoliosis_Imaging">Scoliosis Imaging</span></h3>
<ul><li> Radiology is frequently having to call clinic because we order a 2 view but a 1 view is needed. Here are the guidelines:
<ol><li> Order a 1 view x-ray if you are getting a baseline or to see if the curvature is increasing.</li>
<li> Order a 2 view if the patient is post-op scoliosis surgery or if you think the patient has a kyphotic curve.</li></ol></li></ul>

